article.headline: St. John's 80, Bryant 44
article.story: NEW YORK -- D.J. Kennedy scored 18 points to lead St. John's in an 80-44 rout of winless Bryant University on Wednesday night. Dwight Hardy and Paris Horne added 16 points apiece for the Red Storm (10-2), who bounced back from a 71-66 loss to Cornell in the championship game of the Holiday Festival at Madison Square Garden on Monday night. Horne finished 5-for-6 on 3-pointers. After taking a 12-point lead early, the Bulldogs (0-12) pulled even at 14-all with just over 13 minutes to play in the first half. After a St. John's timeout, Kennedy and Hardy hit back to back 3s to help spark a 29-7 run the rest of the period. The Red Storm outscored Bryant 37-23 in the second half. The Bulldogs had 12 players score, but none finished in double figures. St. John's has won four of its last five games after opening the season with six consecutive wins.
